Rating: 4
This has been a staple among all dishes. Easy to prepare and presents elegantly. I undercook the tenderloin slightly then cover it with foil. Deglaze the cast iron skillet with red wine add a few shallots, a bit of beef stock and reduce. The sauce is strained and returned to skillet with addition of a few pats of butter. I slice the tenderloin thinly and serve on a bed of orzo cooked risotto style with a finish of 1 cup parmesan. Then drizzle gravy over the pork and serve remaining gravy in a sauce boat. Always gets rave responses!

