Rating: 4
Great recipe! Roasted potatoes were an excellent side dish. Peel and quarter potatoes, coat with olive oil and roast in a 400 degree oven for about 45 minutes. Turn several times, particularly at the beginning (they will tend to stick). When the pork is ready to go into the oven, transfer the potatoes to the skillet. Turn the potatoes when you turn the pork to get them golden and crispy on all sides.

